                            <comment id="16930249" author="rivanov" created="Mon, 16 Sep 2019 06:12:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A casting to the class somehow workarounds the issue:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
list.each {
    myClass.myField = ((MyClass) myClass).myField
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16932938" author="daniel_sun" created="Thu, 19 Sep 2019 00:11:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It works with groovy 3.0.0-beta-3. I think some fixes are not merged into 2_5_X branch, because they are very hard to merge...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16932991" author="rivanov" created="Thu, 19 Sep 2019 02:09:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your prompt response, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=daniel_sun&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;daniel_sun&quot;&gt;daniel_sun&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You see, we would not like to jump on a pre-stable versions but on latest stable and vulnerable free ones. As 2.5.x is the latest stable release, could you merge a fix for 2.5.9. Moreover, when it is expected 2.5.9 and 3.0.0 to be GA?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16943704" author="emilles" created="Thu, 3 Oct 2019 16:27:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not able to recreate using Groovy 2.5.7 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://groovyconsole.appspot.com&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://groovyconsole.appspot.com&lt;/a&gt;) or 2.5.8 or current 2_5_X branch.  Are there additional settings/circumstances besides the script you have posted?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16943713" author="emilles" created="Thu, 3 Oct 2019 16:32:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I enable static compilation, then this exhibits the same issue as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9265&quot; title=&quot;ScriptMain.groovy: -1: Access to bugs.ClassWithInnerClass$InnerClass#obj is forbidden @ line -1, column -1.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-9265&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-9265&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  There is a pull request to fix resolution of local variables from within closures under static compilation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16945672" author="rivanov" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2019 08:17:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilles&quot;&gt;emilles&lt;/a&gt;, it is static compilation indeed. Can you try reproducing it with static compilation?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That looks as a serious problem so could we have a fix in next stable version as well? We do not want to jump on release candidate/unstable version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16946004" author="emilles" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2019 16:24:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9265&quot; title=&quot;ScriptMain.groovy: -1: Access to bugs.ClassWithInnerClass$InnerClass#obj is forbidden @ line -1, column -1.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-9265&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-9265&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has been merged to master and 3_0_X.  It just needs to be merged to 2_5_X and you will see a fix in Groovy 2.5.9.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16946302" author="rivanov" created="Mon, 7 Oct 2019 22:38:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Awesome for 2.5.9. Thank you, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilles&quot;&gt;emilles&lt;/a&gt; When it is supposed to come 2.5.9?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16960693" author="rivanov" created="Sun, 27 Oct 2019 23:49:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilles&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilles&quot;&gt;emilles&lt;/a&gt;, could you please answer the question when closing the ticket? Moreover, having set the fix version to &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/issues/?jql=project+%3D+GROOVY+AND+fixVersion+%3D+3.0.0-rc-1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;3.0.0-rc-1&lt;/a&gt;&quot;, are you planning not to include a fix in 2.5.9?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16982964" author="rivanov" created="Tue, 26 Nov 2019 22:26:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will that be fixed in 2.5.9?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16983055" author="paulk" created="Wed, 27 Nov 2019 01:06:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The following example works in 3.0.0-rc-1 and works on the GROOVY_2_5_X branch so will work in 2.5.9 and above as per the fix versions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyClass {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; myField
}
@groovy.transform.CompileStatic
def method() {
  MyClass myClass = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; MyClass()
  [].each {
    myClass.myField = myClass.myField &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// BOOM!!!
&lt;/span&gt;  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have no exact date scheduled for 2.5.9 but I expect in the next 1-4 weeks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
